```java
@Override
public CompletionStage<Void> register(String uri, String sessionId, String nodeId, Map<String, String> metadata) {
    return CompletableFuture.runAsync(() -> {
        try {
            kv.put(sessionKey(uri, sessionId), nodeId.getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8));  // Line 85: session key first
            kv.put(memberKey(nodeId, uri, sessionId), new byte[0]);                          // Line 86: membership key second
        } catch (Exception e) {
            throw new java.util.concurrent.CompletionException("NATS KV register failed", e);
        }
    }, executor);
}
```

Lines 143-164 (removeAllForNode method):
```java
@Override
public CompletionStage<Void> removeAllForNode(String nodeId) {
    return CompletableFuture.runAsync(() -> {
        try {
            String prefix = "n." + b64(nodeId) + ".";
            for (String key : kv.keys()) {
                if (key.startsWith(prefix)) {
                    // key = n.<b64(nodeId)>.<b64(uri)>.<sessionId>
                    String rest = key.substring(prefix.length());
                    int dot = rest.lastIndexOf('.');
                    if (dot > 0) {
                        String b64uri = rest.substring(0, dot);
                        String sessionId = rest.substring(dot + 1);
                        kv.delete("s." + b64uri + "." + sessionId);
                    }
                    kv.delete(key);
                }
            }
        } catch (Exception ex) {
            throw new java.util.concurrent.CompletionException("NATS KV removeAllForNode failed", ex);
        }
    }, executor);
}
```

Problem: register() writes session key (line 85) then membership key (line 86). If the membership-key put (line 86) fails after the session-key put succeeds, the session key is orphaned. The removeAllForNode() cleanup ONLY iterates membership keys (line 146: prefix search for "n." keys) and reconstructs session keys from them (line 155), so orphaned session keys cannot be cleaned up.

validations.fixApproach:
Chain deregister and deadNodeCallback on successful completion of removeAllForNode. The fix should:
1. Call removeAllForNode(deadNodeId) and capture the returned CompletionStage
2. Chain thenRun() or thenAccept() to execute heartbeat.deregister() and the callback only after cleanup succeeds
3. Handle exceptions: on cleanup failure, either log and skip (relying on re-detection on next sweep) or leave the node un-reaped so a later sweep retries

Example structure:
```
CompletionStage<Void> cleanup = sessionRegistry.removeAllForNode(deadNodeId);
cleanup.thenRun(() -> {
    heartbeat.deregister(deadNodeId);
    // notify callback
}).exceptionally(ex -> {
    log.warn("Failed to clean up sessions for dead node {}", deadNodeId, ex);
    return null;
});
```

The reconciliation task remains non-blocking (it schedules async work without waiting), but the sequencing is now correct.

